    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Located adjacent to the San Francisco Bay, Alameda is a mid-sized California city, with
a population of about 73,800. As with many places in California, Alameda is close to
the Pacific Ocean, and has been nicknamed, "The Island City". Alameda provides many
outdoor and water activities, such as wind surfing or kite surfing. With multiple parks
and recreational areas, most outdoor sports can be played locally. Known for its Victorian
charm, tree-lined streets, and mild climate, there is a lot to see and do. Listed as one of the
top ten American, "Coolest Suburbs Worth a Visit", Alameda is home to several theaters,
museums, historical sites, concerts, street festivals and farm. With so much to see and
experience, there is no shortage of fun to be had in Alameda!</p>
